ament allegorically and typologically. Origen distinguishes between a literal and a figurative, moral-spiritual interpretation of the Holy Scripture. Especially in the case of his sermons on the Book of Genesis it is fascinating to follow how Origen as teacher and pastor attempts to convey to the congregation the many different aspects of holy insights, from cosmology to the allegorical interpretation of Lot’s wife being turned into a pillar of salt.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Modern (1453â€“).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aSermons, LatinvTranslations into German. 4aAltes Testament. 4aBibelexegese. 4aGenesis. 4aOrigenes. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / Exegesis & Hermeneutics.2bisacsh  aBible Exegesis.  aGenesis.  aOld Testament.  aOrigen.1 aHabermehl, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2011z9783110261189oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2011z9783110261271oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311020435340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311022599040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110225990423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110225990/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2011  aZDB-23-DGGb2011  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014